15/08/2006
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Three people -- two women and a child -- were injured in an explosion in a park in Istanbul's historic quarter of Sultanahmet on Monday (14 August).
Police say the three victims, all relatives, were on a holiday in Istanbul.
All are in hospital.
No group has claimed responsibility for the blast.
In other news Monday, Istanbul police announced that they detained 14 supporters of the Kurdistan Workers' Party.
Authorities say the group held an illegal rally in the Istanbul quarter of Umraniye the previous evening.
(Zaman - 15/08/06;
NTV, Cihan - 14/08/06)
